This paper is about building a type checker for a programming language, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of formal specification and proof assistants, which are related to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the syntax and semantics of the Jolie programming language, which could be classified under formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
